<ArticleLayout
  locale="en"
  title="Demo SEO Landing Page"
  description="A template landing page demonstrating the recommended SEO content structure."
  updated="2026-06-28"
>
  <h2>What Is This Tool?</h2>
  <p>
    This is a demo landing page that shows how a static SEO tool page can explain its purpose before asking the visitor to use it.
    Use it as a template when creating real landing pages for browser-based tools.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Use</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Enter your input.</li>
    <li>Click the button.</li>
    <li>Copy or download the result.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <p>
    Before: a visitor has raw text, numbers, or settings that need cleanup.
    After: the page returns a clearer result that can be copied, saved, or used in the next step.
  </p>

  <h2>Use Cases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Creating a clear landing page for a new utility.</li>
    <li>Explaining who the tool is for before showing the controls.</li>
    <li>Adding examples that help search visitors understand the outcome.</li>
    <li>Preparing a page structure that can later support FAQ and related links.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Note: FAQ and related links should be added when converting this demo into a real landing page.
  </p>

  <p class="privacy-note">
    Privacy note: this demo represents tools that run in the browser, so visitor input does not need to be sent to a server.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
